Collection.ClinicalDescription: Mid cells may include less frequently occurring and rare cells such as monocytes, eosinophils, basophils, blasts and other precursor WBC's.

Collection.Name: LDL
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
National Cholesterol Education Program, ATP III recommendations:
 Optimal:               <130 mg/dL
                       (<100 mg/dL if patient has CHD)
  Borderline High:    130 - 159 mg/dL
  High Risk:           160 - 189 mg/dL
  Very High Risk:      >189 mg/dL

Collection.Name: Triglycerides
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
National Cholesterol Education Program, ATP III recommendations:
    Normal Fasting    <150 mg/dL
    Borderline High    150 - 199 mg/dL
    High                200 - 499 mg/dL
    Very High           >499 mg/dL

Collection.Name: Cholesterol/HDL Ratio
Collection.ClinicalDescription: Desirable ratio is below 5.0        Optimum ratio is 3.5

Collection.Name: HDL
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
National Cholesterol Education Program, ATP III, recommendations:
HDL less than 40 mg/dL suggests higher risk. HDL 60 mg/dL or greater is considered to be a negative risk factor.

Collection.Name: Cholesterol, Total
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
National Cholesterol Education Program, ATP III recommendations:
Desirable  <200 mg/dL in adults
<170 mg/dL in adolescents and children
Borderline High  200 - 239 mg/dL
 High >239 mg/dL
